00:16:00,824 --> 00:16:06,424
離さないで、物語は一歩先へ
Don't let go, the story is one step ahead.

183
00:16:07,424 --> 00:16:13,624
諦めてしまうほど この先たくさんの 後悔が君を待ってるけど
There's so much regret waiting ahead that you might give up, but...

184
00:16:14,124 --> 00:16:18,624
もう迷わない、迷いはしないよ
I won't be lost, I won't get lost anymore.

185
00:16:18,824 --> 00:16:22,824
この傷も愛しく思えてしまうほど
To the point where even these scars feel precious,

186
00:16:22,824 --> 00:16:25,124
重なってしまうよ
They keep piling up.

187
00:16:25,124 --> 00:16:26,624
不格好なままでいいから
It's fine to stay unpolished.

188
00:16:26,824 --> 00:16:29,124
走れ その歩幅で
Run at your own pace!

189
00:16:29,124 --> 00:16:31,824
走れ 声を響かせてくれ
Run! Let your voice ring out!

190
00:16:32,124 --> 00:16:36,624
期待と不安を同じくらい抱きしめて
Embracing expectation and anxiety in equal measure,

191
00:16:36,824 --> 00:16:39,624
刻んだ今を 紡ぐ未来 足して
Adding this carved moment to the future we weave.

192
00:17:07,924 --> 00:17:10,124
ありがとうー！
Thank you!

193
00:17:11,124 --> 00:17:13,124
改めて、おめでとう！
Once again, congratulations!

194
00:17:13,624 --> 00:17:15,624
ありがとうー！
Thank you!

195
00:17:16,124 --> 00:17:19,624
待って、そういえば自己紹介してなくね？
Wait, come to think of it, haven't we introduced ourselves?

196
00:17:19,624 --> 00:17:20,624
あー、確かに。
Oh, you're right.

197
00:17:20,624 --> 00:17:21,824
誰ですか？
Who are you guys?

198
00:17:22,124 --> 00:17:28,124
可愛いポジティブジーニアス、火威青の女、一条莉々華です！
I'm the cute positive genius and Ao Hiodoshi's girl, Ririka Ichijou!

199
00:17:28,124 --> 00:17:31,124
火威青の女！？
Ao Hiodoshi's girl!?

200
00:17:33,624 --> 00:17:37,824
へっぽこ番長、轟はじめ、えー、火威青のお姉ちゃんよ！
I'm the clumsy delinquent leader, Hajime Todoroki, and Ao's big sister!

201
00:17:37,824 --> 00:17:42,124
お姉ちゃんじゃねーよ！火威青なんだわ！
I'm not your big sister! I'm Ao Hiodoshi!

202
00:17:43,824 --> 00:17:50,424
ReGLOSSの儒烏風亭らでんでございます。えー、音乃瀬奏の...コーチ？
I'm Raden Juufuutei from ReGLOSS. And I'm Kanade Otonose's... coach?

203
00:17:50,624 --> 00:17:53,124
コーチ！？何を教えたの！？
Coach!? What did you teach her!?

204
00:17:53,624 --> 00:17:57,124
教わった記憶ないんですけど。見なよ、こっちがコーチな。
I don't remember being taught anything. Look, I'm the coach here.

205
00:17:57,124 --> 00:18:01,424
逆な、それ。
It's the other way around.

206
00:18:02,124 --> 00:18:08,124
ReGLOSSのみんな、来てくれてありがとうー！
Everyone from ReGLOSS, thank you so much for coming!

207
00:18:08,624 --> 00:18:10,824
この曲歌いたかったんだー。
I've really wanted to sing this song.

208
00:18:11,124 --> 00:18:12,124
嬉しい。
I'm so happy.

209
00:18:12,124 --> 00:18:13,824
めっちゃいい曲。
It's such a great song.

210
00:18:13,824 --> 00:18:15,124
ね、最高だった。
Right? It was awesome.

211
00:18:15,124 --> 00:18:18,824
次はゲストパートなんだけど、一緒にコールお願いしてもいいかな？
The next part is the guest part. Can I ask you guys to join the call?

212
00:18:18,824 --> 00:18:20,424
もちろーん！
Of course!

213
00:18:20,624 --> 00:18:24,124
じゃあ行くよ、せーの、どうぞー！
Alright, here we go! One, two, go!

214
00:18:34,124 --> 00:18:36,824
ねえ考えなくていいよ
Hey, you don't have to think about it.

215
00:18:36,824 --> 00:18:39,624
口先じゃわかりあえないの
We can't understand each other with just words.

216
00:18:39,824 --> 00:18:42,124
この音に今は乗ろうよ
Let's just go with the music for now.

217
00:18:42,124 --> 00:18:44,424
忘れないでいたいよ
I want to keep this in my memory.

218
00:18:44,824 --> 00:18:47,424
身体は無彩色レイドバック
Our bodies are colorless and laid back.

219
00:18:47,624 --> 00:18:49,824
ただうねる雨音でグルーヴ
Just grooving to the surging sound of rain.

220
00:18:50,124 --> 00:18:52,624
ずっと二人で暮らそうよ
Let's live together forever,

221
00:18:52,624 --> 00:18:55,424
この夜の隅っこで
in this little corner of the night.

222
00:19:14,824 --> 00:19:17,624
ねえ大概僕らでいいよ
Hey, mostly we're fine as we are.

223
00:19:17,624 --> 00:19:20,424
誘ったのは君じゃないの
It wasn't you who invited me.

224
00:19:20,624 --> 00:19:23,124
理屈だけじゃつまらないわ
Just logic is boring.

225
00:19:23,124 --> 00:19:25,624
まだ時間が欲しいの
I still want more time.

226
00:19:25,824 --> 00:19:28,124
練り歩く景色をシンクバック
Thinking back on the scenery we walked through.

227
00:19:28,124 --> 00:19:30,624
踏み鳴らす足音でグルーヴ
Grooving to the sound of our footsteps.

228
00:19:30,824 --> 00:19:33,124
まるで僕らはブレーメン
It's like we're the Bremen Town Musicians.

229
00:19:33,124 --> 00:19:35,624
たった二人だけの街
In a town of just the two of us.

230
00:19:35,824 --> 00:19:38,624
さあ、息を吸って
Come on, take a breath,

231
00:19:39,124 --> 00:19:41,124
吐いて、吐いて
exhale, exhale.

232
00:19:45,624 --> 00:19:47,824
あ、正々歌ってようぜ
Ah, let's keep singing fair and square.

233
00:19:48,124 --> 00:19:50,424
笑う門には福来るとか
They say fortune comes to those who smile.

234
00:19:50,624 --> 00:19:53,124
愛の歌 奪ってんのさ
We're snatching away the songs of love.

235
00:19:55,624 --> 00:19:58,124
あ、正々楽してこうぜ
Ah, let's just take it easy.

236
00:19:58,624 --> 00:20:01,624
死ぬほどのことはこの世にないぜ
There's nothing in this world worth dying for.

237
00:20:00,272 --> 00:20:01,572
明日は何しようか
What should we do tomorrow?

238
00:20:01,572 --> 00:20:02,772
暇なら笑い合おうぜ
If we're free, let's laugh together.

239
00:20:02,772 --> 00:20:04,672
そのうち分かり合おうぜ
We'll understand each other eventually.

240
00:20:25,472 --> 00:20:27,972
ねぇ考えなくてもいいよ
Hey, you don't have to think about it.

241
00:20:27,972 --> 00:20:30,572
踊り始めた君の細胞
Your cells have started to dance.

242
00:20:30,572 --> 00:20:33,072
この音に今は乗ろうよ
Let's ride this sound for now.

243
00:20:33,072 --> 00:20:35,572
乗れなくてもいいよ
It's okay if you can't ride it.

244
00:20:35,672 --> 00:20:38,172
思い出の景色でバックパック
Backpacking through the scenery of memories.

245
00:20:38,172 --> 00:20:40,672
春風の騒めきでグルーヴ
Grooving with the rustle of the spring breeze.

246
00:20:40,672 --> 00:20:43,172
もっと二人で歌おうよ
Let's sing together more.

247
00:20:43,172 --> 00:20:45,672
暇なら愛をしようよ
If we're free, let's make love.

248
00:20:45,772 --> 00:20:48,272
さぁ 息を吸って
Now, take a breath...

249
00:20:48,272 --> 00:20:50,772
声に出して
...and let it out in your voice.

250
00:20:55,672 --> 00:20:58,272
斉々歌っていようぜ
Let's just keep on singing.

251
00:20:58,272 --> 00:21:00,772
嗤われてるのも仕方ないね
It's okay to be laughed at.

252
00:21:00,772 --> 00:21:03,372
何もかも間違ってんのさ
Everything is wrong anyway.

253
00:21:03,372 --> 00:21:05,872
Ah-ha-ha-ha

254
00:21:05,872 --> 00:21:08,372
斉々楽していこうぜ
Let's just take it easy.

255
00:21:08,372 --> 00:21:10,872
馬鹿なよそ者もラグジュアライズ
Luxurizing even the foolish outsiders.

256
00:21:10,872 --> 00:21:13,372
同じような歌詞だし
The lyrics are all the same anyway.

257
00:21:13,372 --> 00:21:15,972
三番は飛ばしていいよ
You can skip the third verse.

258
00:21:26,472 --> 00:21:28,972
さぁ 息を吸って
Now, take a breath...

259
00:21:28,972 --> 00:21:31,472
早く吐いて
...and exhale quickly.

260
00:21:36,472 --> 00:21:38,972
ねぇ 心を貸して
Hey, lend me your heart...

261
00:21:38,972 --> 00:21:41,472
今日くらいは
...at least for today.

262
00:21:46,372 --> 00:21:48,972
斉々歌っていようぜ
Let's just keep on singing.

263
00:21:48,972 --> 00:21:51,472
違う顔してお前ら皆
All of you, with your different faces...

264
00:21:51,472 --> 00:21:54,072
僕のこと嗤ってんのかい
...are you laughing at me?

265
00:21:56,572 --> 00:21:59,072
斉々楽してこうぜ
Let's just take it easy.

266
00:21:59,072 --> 00:22:01,572
死ぬほど辛いなら逃げ出そうぜ
If it's painful enough to die, let's run away.

267
00:22:01,572 --> 00:22:04,172
数年経てばきっと
In a few years, surely...

268
00:22:04,172 --> 00:22:06,672
一人も覚えてないよ
...no one will remember.

269
00:22:06,672 --> 00:22:09,272
斉々打たれていようぜ
Let's just keep taking the hits.

270
00:22:09,272 --> 00:22:11,772
身体は動く お前もどうだい
My body still moves, how about yours?

271
00:22:11,772 --> 00:22:14,272
哀の歌 歌ってんのさ
I'm singing a song of sorrow.

272
00:22:14,272 --> 00:22:16,872
Ah-ha-ha-ha

273
00:22:16,872 --> 00:22:19,372
斉々楽していこうぜ
Let's just take it easy.

274
00:22:19,372 --> 00:22:21,972
死ぬほどのことはこの世にないぜ
There's nothing in this world worth dying for.

275
00:22:21,972 --> 00:22:24,472
明日は何しようか
What should we do tomorrow?

276
00:22:24,472 --> 00:22:27,072
暇なら笑い合おうぜ
If we're free, let's laugh together.

277
00:22:27,072 --> 00:22:29,572
そのうち分かり合おうぜ
We'll understand each other eventually.

278
00:23:50,272 --> 00:23:55,272
奏 (かなで)
作詞・作曲 大橋卓弥 / 常田真太郎
Kanade
Lyrics & Composition: Takuya Ohashi / Shintaro Tokita

279
00:24:02,672 --> 00:24:05,372
改札の前 つなぐ手と手
In front of the ticket gate, hands joined.

280
00:24:05,372 --> 00:24:08,672
いつものざわめき 新しい風
The usual bustle, a new breeze.

281
00:24:08,672 --> 00:24:14,572
明るく見送るはずだったのに
I was supposed to see you off cheerfully, but...

282
00:24:14,572 --> 00:24:17,572
うまく笑えずに
...I couldn't smile well...

283
00:24:17,572 --> 00:24:20,772
君を見ていた
...and just looked at you.

284
00:24:27,572 --> 00:24:33,872
君が大人になってくその季節が
So that the season when you become an adult...

285
00:24:33,872 --> 00:24:40,172
悲しい歌で溢れないように
...won't be filled with sad songs...

286
00:24:40,172 --> 00:24:45,572
最後に何か君に伝えたくて
...wanting to tell you one last thing at the end...

287
00:24:45,572 --> 00:24:48,572
「さよなら」に代わる言葉を
...for words to replace "goodbye"...

288
00:24:48,572 --> 00:24:53,272
僕は探してた
...I was searching.

289
00:24:58,272 --> 00:25:01,272
君の手を引く
Taking your hand...

290
00:25:00,887 --> 00:25:02,387
…その役目が
...that role of mine

291
00:25:02,687 --> 00:25:06,887
僕の使命だなんて そう思ってた
Was my mission in life, or so I thought

292
00:25:10,387 --> 00:25:13,887
だけど今わかったんだ 僕らならもう
But now I understand; for the two of us,

293
00:25:16,387 --> 00:25:22,887
重ねた日々がほら、導いてくれる
Look, the days we've spent together will guide us.

294
00:25:24,387 --> 00:25:29,887
君が大人になってくその時間が
While the time you spend becoming an adult

295
00:25:30,387 --> 00:25:36,387
降り積もる間に僕も変わってく
Piles up, I will change as well.

296
00:25:36,887 --> 00:25:41,887
たとえばそこにこんな歌があれば
For example, if there were a song like this,

297
00:25:42,887 --> 00:25:49,887
ふたりはいつもどんな時もつながっていける
We could stay connected always, no matter the time.

298
00:26:19,387 --> 00:26:24,387
突然ふいに鳴り響くベルの音
Suddenly, the sound of the departure bell rings out.

299
00:26:25,387 --> 00:26:30,387
焦る僕 解ける手 離れてく君
I panic, our hands part, and you move away.

300
00:26:31,887 --> 00:26:36,887
夢中で呼び止めて 抱きしめたんだ
Frantically, I called out to stop you and held you tight.

301
00:26:37,887 --> 00:26:43,887
君がどこに行ったって僕の声で守るよ
No matter where you go, I will protect you with my voice.

302
00:26:49,387 --> 00:26:53,387
君が僕の前に現れた日から
From the day you first appeared before me,

303
00:26:54,387 --> 00:26:59,887
何もかもが違くみえたんだ
Everything started to look different.

304
00:27:01,387 --> 00:27:06,387
朝も光も涙も、歌う声も
The morning, the light, the tears, and even my singing voice...

305
00:27:07,387 --> 00:27:12,887
君が輝きをくれたんだ
You were the one who gave them their shine.

306
00:27:13,887 --> 00:27:19,387
抑えきれない思いをこの声に乗せて
I'll put these uncontrollable feelings into my voice

307
00:27:20,387 --> 00:27:25,387
遠く君の街へ届けよう
And deliver them to your distant town.

308
00:27:26,387 --> 00:27:31,387
たとえばそれがこんな歌だったら
For example, if it were a song like this,

309
00:27:32,387 --> 00:27:38,887
ぼくらは何処にいたとしてもつながっていける
We could stay connected no matter where we are.

310
00:28:48,887 --> 00:28:52,887
No title / 作詞・作曲: Reol
No title / Lyrics & Music: Reol

311
00:28:57,087 --> 00:28:59,387
ずっと夢見てた僕になれたかな
Have I become the person I always dreamed I'd be?

312
00:28:59,687 --> 00:29:02,387
とうに帰れないとこまで来たみたい
It seems I've come to a point of no return.

313
00:29:02,687 --> 00:29:05,087
自分の足で二段飛ばして
Taking two steps at a time with my own feet,

314
00:29:05,387 --> 00:29:08,387
そうもっと先へ駆けていけるはずだから ran away
I should be able to run further ahead, so I ran away.

315
00:29:08,687 --> 00:29:09,687
深くなる傷を縫い付け
Sewing up the wounds that grow deeper,

316
00:29:09,887 --> 00:29:11,387
繋ぐパス軸に回りだす
I start to spin around the path I connect.

317
00:29:11,887 --> 00:29:14,387
なれた痛み、焦る呼吸とビート
This familiar pain, my frantic breathing and the beat—

318
00:29:14,887 --> 00:29:16,887
気付かないふりしてまた一人
I pretend not to notice and find myself alone again.

319
00:29:17,387 --> 00:29:18,687
何が正当？ないな永劫
What is 'correct'? Nothing lasts forever.

320
00:29:19,387 --> 00:29:21,387
誰が間違った対価払うの
Who will pay the price for the mistakes made?

321
00:29:21,887 --> 00:29:23,887
あんたが嫌いなあいつはきっと
That person you hate is surely

322
00:29:24,387 --> 00:29:26,687
ただ「それだけ」で不正解なんだ
'incorrect' just because of that one thing.

323
00:29:27,087 --> 00:29:28,887
零点だって提言したって
Even if I'm told I've scored a zero,

324
00:29:29,387 --> 00:29:31,387
全然納得できない理由も
The reason I can't accept it at all is because

325
00:29:31,887 --> 00:29:34,087
最前線はいつだってここだった
The front line has always been right here.

326
00:29:34,387 --> 00:29:36,687
最善策は最初からなかった
There was never a 'best strategy' from the start.

327
00:29:37,087 --> 00:29:39,387
緩やかに崩れ壊れてく
Slowly, I'm crumbling and breaking apart.

328
00:29:39,687 --> 00:29:42,087
ゆるりゆるり首を絞めるように
Slowly, slowly, as if being strangled,

329
00:29:42,387 --> 00:29:45,087
昨日までの僕が殺されていく
The 'me' from yesterday is being killed off.

330
00:29:46,687 --> 00:29:49,087
緩やかに離れ離れあく
Gently, we are pulled further apart.

331
00:29:49,387 --> 00:29:52,087
グラリンリ君に聞こえるのは
Swaying and shaking, what you hear

332
00:29:52,387 --> 00:29:55,887
僕が知らない声になってく
Is becoming a voice I no longer recognize.

333
00:30:05,142 --> 00:30:09,542
幼い頃から 気づいたらそばにいた
Since I was little, you've been by my side

334
00:30:10,042 --> 00:30:12,142
まるで空気のようだ
Just like the air itself

335
00:30:12,342 --> 00:30:14,842
僕は君とぎゅっと手を繋いで
I held your hand tightly

336
00:30:15,142 --> 00:30:18,842
楽しいことも涙も 僕は君に話し聞かせた
The fun times and the tears, I told you everything

337
00:30:19,142 --> 00:30:23,842
僕を笑う人 貶す声 掻き消すように 君は歌った
As if to drown out the laughter and disparaging voices, you sang

338
00:30:24,142 --> 00:30:29,142
この声を君が自身の体温で ずっと温めてくれた
You kept this voice of mine warm with your own heat

339
00:30:29,142 --> 00:30:31,342
使い捨てだって 言ってたって
Even if they say it's disposable

340
00:30:31,342 --> 00:30:33,842
止まらないハイファイ タイトロープ
This unstoppable hi-fi tightrope

341
00:30:34,142 --> 00:30:37,842
一周回るものの たった一瞬だけでも
In a whole cycle, even if it's just for a moment

342
00:30:38,142 --> 00:30:41,142
交わる音 繋ぐ色 次は僕が君に歌うんだ
Intersecting sounds, connecting colors, next I'll sing for you

343
00:30:43,842 --> 00:30:47,542
ゆるやかに 崩れ壊れてく
Slowly, it's collapsing and breaking apart

344
00:30:47,842 --> 00:30:52,542
ゆるりゆるり首を絞めるように 昨日までの僕が殺されていく
Slowly, as if tightening a noose, the me from yesterday is killed

345
00:30:53,342 --> 00:30:57,542
ゆるやかに 離れ離れを
Slowly drifting apart

346
00:30:57,842 --> 00:31:02,342
ぷらり君に聞こえるのは 僕が知らない声になっていく
What you hear as you drift away is becoming a voice I don't know

347
00:31:02,842 --> 00:31:06,842
ゆるやかに 崩れ壊れてく
Slowly, it's collapsing and breaking apart

348
00:31:07,142 --> 00:31:11,842
ゆるりゆるり首を絞めるように 昨日までの僕が殺されていく
Slowly, as if tightening a noose, the me from yesterday is killed

349
00:31:12,542 --> 00:31:16,842
ゆるやかに 離れ離れを
Slowly drifting apart

350
00:31:17,142 --> 00:31:21,842
ぷらり君に聞こえるのは 僕が知らない声になっていく
What you hear as you drift away is becoming a voice I don't know

351
00:31:22,342 --> 00:31:24,342
いつか君に届くかな
Will it reach you someday?

352
00:31:24,342 --> 00:31:26,842
いや そんな日はきっと来ないだろうな
No, that day will surely never come

